extends base.pug

block scripts
    script(src='/static/index.js')

block style
    style
        include ../static/style.css

block content
    section#intro
            div Welcome to PRINCE Dance Academy
            div.small Eat Dance Sleep Repeat
    section#mission
            h2 Our Mission
            div.card
                h3 Dance Perfection
                div.card-box
                    div.card-img
                        img(src="/static/img/d1.png", alt="")

                div.card-content1
                    p Dance is a performing art form consisting of purposefully selected sequences of human movement. This movement has aesthetic and symbolic value, and is acknowledged as dance by performers and observers within a particular culture. Dance can be categorized and described by its choreography.
            div.card
                h3 Learn the way you like to dance 
                div.card-box
                    div.card-img
                        img(src="/static/img/d3.png", alt="")

                div.card-content2
                    p Dance is a performing art. It is described in many ways. It is when people move to a musical rhythm. They may be alone, or in a group. The dance may be an informal play, a part of a ritual, or a part of a professional performance.
            div.card
                h3 Expert Teaching  
                div.card-box
                    div.card-img
                        img(src="/static/img/d6.png", alt="")

                div.card-content3
                    p A dance teacher communicates theory and practice of any one of a number of dance disciplines to students. Since time immemorial humankind has danced. Be it for celebration, social interaction or to express a deeper concept related to the human condition that is inexpressible.
    
    section#sasura
            h3 Our Sponsors
                div#spon
                    img(src="/static/img/microsoft.png", alt="sponsors", class="prince")
                    img(src="/static/img/d11.png", alt="sponsors", class="prince")
                    img(src="/static/img/fb.png", alt="sponsors", class="prince")